        "subject": "LU-2266 tests: Wait for client reconnect in recovery-small 27",
        "message": "LU-2266 tests: Wait for client reconnect in recovery-small 27\n\nIn commit de311fb7 a bug was introduced where we no longer wait\nfor client reconnect and instead the check is such that the client\nhave not attempted reconnect yet. As such the test is a noop most\nof the time.\nCorrect the waiting condition to include CFS_FAILED mask.\n\nAdditinally fixed a race where MDS might reconnect to OST faster than\nwhen we are able to set fail_loc (which is very possible on multinode\nsetup, original test was designed for a single node test)\n(I belive this should also work on 32bit clients, since we converted to\nprinting unsigned longs now)\n\nAlso fix signed-unsigned issue in proc_fail_loc\n\nChange-Id: I3502e17184016a5c526b77a37cc7b505d8bfd5ed\nSigned-off-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
